#wow Absolutely stunning! 🙌  @justbitters
・・・
“Six years ago, @Dennis_Gobis and I started working on this idea for a cocktail truck built inside a French Citroën HY Van that could execute the same level of cocktails as we do at @RooseveltRoomATX  We never thought it would have taken us so long to find the truck, get it restored, have it shipped over the Atlantic, get it up to Austin, plan every quarter inch of its buildout, find a fabricator crazy enough to take on the job, wait for them to build it out during covid, plan out all of the equipment/glassware/storage/etc., figure out we needed a trailer to serve as the BOH (which came with planning that out to the square inch, etc. etc.), and the list goes on. But, here we are, about to launch a true passion project, RoadHaus Mobile Cocktails @RoadHausMC and all of the painstaking hours of planning, fixing, redoing, planning again, failing again, learning, etc. are about to pay off. We'll be launching in a few weeks, and I don't think "excited" could even come close to capturing the full emotion I have about finally working in and on this unique concept. Time to get this thing rollin'! 

P.S. Having had six years to develop its marketing plan, the number of vehicle/driving/motion/etc. puns that apply to this thing is daunting. I have a list of around 300, but if you have any you'd like to share, I'm all ears!... “
